Class Gene<E>

java.lang.Object

              com.tabuto.jenetic.Gene<E>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>, java.util.RandomAccess
public class Gene<E>
extends java.util.Vector<E>

Gene<E> is a Generics Class wrapper for any object type. It can contains and returns objects. Gene auto recognize the wrapped Object Class and set mergeable flag as true in order to let Dna Class make a Gene Recombination; This is possible only if the wrapped Object is a primitive type such as: Integer, Double, Boolean, Byte.

Version:
0.2.3
Author:
tabuto83
